        <div class="rightbox">
            <div class="sectiontitle"><a href="https://vimeo.com/phoebeoh/" target="_blank">ANIMATED SHORTS;</a></div>
            <div class="workcategory">interactive animation</div>
        </div>
        <div id="work">
            As an animation student, I've created several short films over the years. These are my favorites!
            <p>
            <div id="workbox">
            <div id="workleft"></div>
            <div id="workright">
            <a href="https://vimeo.com/381385330" target="_blank"><b>junk drawer (2020):</b></a>
            <ul>
                <li>2d animated short film</li>
                <li>focuses on the forgotten trinkets that carry our mundane, personal, and most treasured memories</li>
                <li>inspired in part by the work of films such as Lulu Wang's "The Farewell"</li>
                <li>assets made from paper cut outs, photographs, and digital illustrations</li>
                <li>animated and composited in adobe aftereffects</li>
                <li>sfx captured with a zoom recorder and mixed with self-composed music in reaper</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="workimg2">
                <img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/c97e7c1acebcddaf022c9d6fee865d86/372b09a6426d2764-e0/s1280x1920/f8544c501f41d430438816e0221635ae2c9d2cd3.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <p><a href="https://vimeo.com/371709471" target="_blank"><b>when in the system (2019):</b></a>
            <ul>
                <li>video remix inspired by the idea of "assimilation is death"</li>
                <li>details the experience faced by many 2nd/3rd generation immigrants who turn on their culture - and the people in it - in order to survive in western society</li>
                <li>digital illustrations and animations created in photoshop</li>
                <li>featured footage with recordings of popular culture icon pac-man characters and clips from the "The Battle of Algiers" - a 1966 film describing the warfare between Muslims and the National Liberation Front against the French Algerian authorities and all the cultural tensions between them</li>
                <li>animated and composited in aftereffects</li>
                <li>music created in reaper</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="workimg2"><img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/69c45a0c96ad1ce99b10c764289258ba/a1d8509bcc3fd1bd-7f/s1280x1920/e8931bf4e16beaa50909e780743edf6e9eb30d7d.png" /></div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <p><a href="https://vimeo.com/442252898" target="_blank"><b>identity (2019):</b></a>
            <ul>
                <li>experimental animation responding to the question, "Who am I?"</li>
                <li>digital hand drawn animation, paper stop motion, multiplane paint on glass, and video footage</li>
                <li>composited in aftereffects</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="workimg2">
                <img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/723f14ae23992ac9f9d1e3ef22ca34ee/372b09a6426d2764-6e/s1280x1920/e6d1d29136ff20b4e98d49fc7a5eeb179bb62e9e.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <p><a href="https://vimeo.com/371683806" target="_blank"><b>lunchbox (2018):</b></a>
            <ul>
                <li>2D animation about celebrating a birthday alone and away from family for the first time. for this piece, I drew upon my own experiences as a university freshman learning how to re-experience events alone - or with friends - when I had been used to sharing them with my family.</li>
                <li>digital illustrations and animations created in photoshop</li>
                <li>composited in aftereffects</li>
                <li>music created in reaper</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="workimg2">
                <img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/4d6c9c3ce47f6fed5541806668a1caca/372b09a6426d2764-33/s1280x1920/68bd5668bb099c03e3395adb7f155b1e1890c7c9.png" />
            </div>
            <p>
            </div>
            </div>
